  1. GET /api/users
     ├─ README  : "List all users"
     ├─ Main    : server.addRoute("/api/users", UsersController.handle)
     └─ Handler : case "GET" => serialises the in-memory `users` list
                  to JSON and returns HTTP 200.
     ✅ Documented AND fully implemented. Consistent.
  
  2. POST /api/users
     ├─ README  : "Create a new user"
     ├─ Main    : same route registration (method dispatch is in handler)
     └─ Handler : case "POST" => // TODO: parse body, validate, add user
                                 Response(201, {"status":"created"})
     ⚠️  Documented AND registered, but the implementation is a stub.
        No request body is parsed, no user is actually created, and
        the in-memory list is never modified. The README's own TODO
        list acknowledges "Add input validation on POST".
  
  3. GET /api/health
     ├─ README  : "Health check"
     ├─ Main    : server.addRoute("/api/health", _ => Response(200, "OK"))
     └─ Handler : inline lambda — returns HTTP 200 "OK" immediately.
     ✅ Documented AND fully implemented. Consistent.
  
